20/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Parliament Speaker Natasa Micic said Sunday (19 October) that early general elections will likely be held soon. In an interview with <I>Vesti</I>, she said that should the ruling coalition, the Democratic Opposition of Serbia, lose two votes of confidence -- in the government and the speaker -- then early elections would be placed on the agenda. Micic and the government are to face no-confidence votes Wednesday.
In other news, Serbian Interior Minister Dusan Mihajlovic confirmed Sunday that Serbian police are ready to participate in the international peacekeeping mission in Afghanistan. All they need, he said, is the go-ahead from the government. (B92, Vesti, BBC, Beta - 19/10/03)
